{{Infobox dot-com company |name = Baboom |logo = Baboomlogo.jpg.png |logo size = <!-- width in pixels, with "px" suffix --> |logo alt = |collapsible = <!-- "yes" or "no" --> |screenshot = |screenshot size = <!-- width in pixels, with "px" suffix --> |screenshot alt = |caption = |type = |traded as = |founded = <!-- {{start date and age|year|month|day}} --> |dissolved = <!-- {{start date and age|year|month|day}} --> |predecessor = |successor = |location = |coordinates = |country = [[Porto]], [[Avenida da Boavista]] |country of origin = Portugal |locations = |area served = |founder = [[Kim Dotcom]] |chairman = |chairperson = |president = |CEO = |MD = |GM = |key people = |industry = |products = |services = |revenue = |operating income = |international = Yes |net income = |assets = |equity = |owner = |employees = |parent = |divisions = |subsidiaries = |slogan = |url = |programming language = |ipv6 = |alexa = |website type = |advertising = |registration = |users = |language = [[English language|English]] |launched = {{start date and age|2015|8|17}} |current status = Shutdown |native clients = [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]] |footnotes = }} '''Baboom''' is a music service based in Portugal. The service was founded by [[Kim Dotcom]], although Baboom and Dotcom severed ties almost a year before the service's launch.<ref name="Dotcom sells out of Baboom">{{cite web|title=Dotcom sells out of Baboom|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/10571753/Dotcom-sells-out-of-Baboom|website=Stuff.co.nz|accessdate=30 September 2015}}</ref> Baboom was launched on 17 August 2015. Baboom described the service as a "Music marketplace that combines Fair Trade Streaming with a music store".<ref name="About">{{cite web|title=About |url=https://baboom.com/about |website=Baboom |accessdate=18 August 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930192528/https://baboom.com/about |archivedate=30 September 2015 }}</ref> The service however was quickly put on hold "until further notice", as stated on Baboom's website, even before it could celebrate its first year.
== Model == Baboom's website states that fans (users) can play the music they want on any device, own the music forever, support artist and be part of the "inner circle", Upload their own music, which include Lossless format.<ref name="About"/>
It also states the service gives artists 90% of the revenue, fair trade streaming, premium following, a right management system and a career analytics system.<ref name="About"/>
Russel Brown of the ''Public Address'' blog said in a review that: {{quote|the most interesting thing about Baboom is the way it addresses some of the problems with the streaming market we've discussed here in recent weeks. Its "fair trade streaming" model works in a fundamentally different way to Spotify et al.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://publicaddress.net/hardnews/baboom-its-serious/ | title=Baboom: it's serious | work=Public Address | accessdate=31 August 2015}}</ref>}}
== Apps == The service supports both [[iOS]] and [[Android (operating system)|Android]]. The apps at the time has limited functionality, with only allowing to listen to music, as well as to download, but at the time of writing have no search function.
