{{Spanish name|Iturralde|González}} {{Infobox football official | name = Eduardo Iturralde González | fullname = Eduardo Iturralde González | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1967|2|20}} | birth_place = [[Arrankudiaga]], [[Biscay]], [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque]], Spain | death_date = | death_place = | otheroccupation = [[Prosthodontics|Prosthodontist]] | years1 = 1995-2012 | league1 = [[La Liga]] | role1 = [[Referee (association football)|Referee]] | internationalyears1 = 1998-2012 | confederation1 = [[FIFA International Referees List|FIFA listed]] | internationalrole1 = Referee }}
'''Eduardo Iturralde González''' (born 20 February 1967 in [[Arrankudiaga]]) is a retired Spanish [[Referee (association football)|football referee]].
He frequently referees European matches in the [[Europa League]] and [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]. Iturralde notably refereed the [[El Clásico]] on three occasions, in 1999, 2005<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mourinho: Barcelona happier with choice of referee |url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2010/11/29/mourinho-barcelona-happier-with-choice-referee.html |quote=Eduardo Iturralde Gonzalez has refereed two games between the teams, with Barcelona winning both times, in 1999 and 2005. |publisher=www.thejakartapost.com |date=29 November 2010 |accessdate=30 November 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101201222531/http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2010/11/29/mourinho-barcelona-happier-with-choice-referee.html |archivedate=1 December 2010 |df= }}</ref> and most recently in November 2010, in which he was praised for his solid and free-flowing performance.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Referee Watch: Eduardo Iturralde González In The Clasico Between Barcelona And Real Madrid |url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/88/spain/2010/11/29/2238093/referee-watch-eduardo-iturralde-gonzalez-in-the-clasico |publisher=goal.com |date=30 November 2010 |accessdate=30 November 2010}}</ref>
Iturralde González was the referee of the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]]'s 2&ndash;1 win over [[Armenia national football team|Armenia]] in the last [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying|Euro 2012 qualifying]] match. Early in the game, he sent off Armenian goalkeeper [[Roman Berezovsky]] for a handball, although video replays indicated that the ball hit his chest.<ref name="Protest">{{cite news |url= http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/sport/2011/1014/1224305756276.html |title=Armenia file protest to Uefa over goalkeeper's red card |date=14 October 2011 |work=[[Irish Times]] |accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref> Two days after the match, the [[Football Federation of Armenia]] officially filed a protest to UEFA over the goalkeeper's dismissal.<ref name="Protest"/>{{Update after|2016|11|17|reason=What was the result? Is it notable enough for inclusion i.e. was it upheld.}}
On March 23, 2012, he announced his retirement from refereeing due to disagreements with the Spanish Technical Committee, although it was already time for him to retire at the end of the 2011–12 season. His last game was Real Betis vs Real Madrid (2–3) on March 10, 2012. He could not finish this game due to a muscle injury, being substituted by the fourth referee, Gorka Sagués Oscoz, during half time.
