[[Fritz Lang]] (1890–1976) was an Austrian [[film director]], [[Film producer|producer]] and [[screenwriter]]. In Lang's early career he worked primarily as a screenwriter, finishing film scripts in four to five days.<ref>Eisner, 1986. p.407</ref> Lang went on to direct popular films of the [[silent era]] including ''Metropolis'' and one of the first important German [[sound films]], ''[[M (1931 film)|M]]''.<ref name="amg">{{cite web|url=http://allmovie.com/artist/fritz-lang-98675/bio|work=Allmovie|accessdate=March 12, 2010|author=Ankeny, Jason|title=Fritz Lang > Biography - Allmovie}}</ref><ref name="Grant">Grant, 2007. p.71</ref> Lang went on to direct some of the most important [[crime film|crime]] and [[film noir]] film of the American studio era, such as ''[[The Big Heat]]''.<ref name="Grant" /> Lang's final film work was an acting role as himself in [[Jean-Luc Godard]]'s ''[[Contempt (film)|Contempt]]''. Lang returned to America to live out his remaining years.<ref name="amg" />
