{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}} {{Use Indian English|date=November 2016}} '''Honey Chhaya''' (1930 &ndash; 28 February 2016) was Indian writer, actor and director. He directed and acted in both [[Hindi film industry|Hindi]] and [[Gujarati cinema|Gujarati films]] and [[Gujarati theatre|plays]].
==Life== Honey Chhaya was born in 1930. He started his acting career in 1944. Initially, he acted in street plays spreading the message of the [[Indian independence movement]]. Later, he started producing plays for the [[Indian People's Theatre Association]]. He had a long career association with [[Salim Khan]], whom he assisted in film writing. He was also a business secretary of [[Salman Khan]] and served a critical role in building his career.<ref name="Naresh 2016">{{cite web | author=Naresh | title=સલમાન ખાનની કરીઅરના પથદર્શકનું નિધન | website=Gujarati Midday | date=29 February 2016 | url=http://www.gujaratimidday.com/mumbai-local/mumbai-local/veteran-actor-honey-chhaya-passes-away | language=gu | accessdate=29 February 2016}}</ref><ref name="jb2016">{{cite web| title=Janamabhoomi : Gujarati News | website=Janmabhoomi| date=29 February 2016 | url=http://www.janmabhoominewspapers.com/article.aspx?site_id=1&news_id=110518 | language=gu | accessdate=29 February 2016}}</ref>
He directed several Gujarati films and plays. He brought [[Chhel Vayeda]]-Paresh Daru in production design career.<ref name="Naresh 2016"/> He wrote a column on [[forensic science]] in Gujarati weekly; ''Janmabhoomi Pravasi''. He acted in several TV commercials.<ref name="jb2016"/> He died on 28 February 2016 5:45 pm at Cardinal Gracias Memorial Hospital, [[Vasai]], Mumbai after a brief illness.<ref name="Naresh 2016"/><ref name="bhaskar2016">{{cite web | title=Veteran Actor Honey Chhaya Passes Away | website=mdaily.bhaskar.com | date=2016-02-29 | url=http://mdaily.bhaskar.com/news-ht/ENT-BOW-veteran-actor-honey-chhaya-passes-away-5261444-PHO.html?referrer_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.co.in%2F | accessdate=2016-02-29}}</ref>
==Personal life== He was married to Manisha. He had a son, Bibhas Chhaya and a daughter, Neerja. Bibhas Chhaya is associated with the film production company of Salman Khan.<ref name="Naresh 2016"/><ref name="jb2016"/>
