{{Infobox Officeholder | name = Margaret Menzies Thom | image = | caption = | office = [[Commissioner of the Northwest Territories]] | term_start = September 18, 2017 | term_end = | predecessor= [[Gerald W. Kisoun]] {{small|(acting)}} | successor = | primeminister = [[Justin Trudeau]] | premier = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Fort Providence, Northwest Territories]] | nationality = | spouse = | children = 4 | occupation = counsellor | religion = }} '''Margaret Menzies{{citation needed|date=November 2018}} Thom''' is the [[Commissioners of the Northwest Territories|Commissioner of the Northwest Territories]].<ref>[http://www.gazette.gc.ca/rp-pr/p1/2017/2017-07-01/html/order-decret-eng.body.html#od2 ORDERS IN COUNCIL]</ref> She previously served as the Deputy Commissioner of the [[Northwest Territories]], Canada, from June 2, 2005, until October 2011.
